#. <section class="sutta" id="sn55.17"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn55.17:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 55"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 55"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.17:0.2"
msgid "2. Rājakārāmavagga"
msgstr "2. A Thousand Nuns"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 17. Dutiyamittāmaccasutta → mittenāmaccā 2 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.17:0.3"
msgid "17. Dutiyamittāmaccasutta"
msgstr "17. Friends and Colleagues (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.17:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Ye te, bhikkhave, anukampeyyātha, ye ca sotabbaṃ maññeyyuṃ—mittā vā amaccā "
"vā ñātī vā sālohitā vā—te, bhikkhave, catūsu sotāpattiyaṅgesu samādapetabbā, "
"nivesetabbā, patiṭṭhāpetabbā."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, those who you have sympathy for, and those worth listening to—"
"friends and colleagues, relatives and family—should be encouraged, "
"supported, and established in the four factors of stream-entry."

msgctxt "sn55.17:1.2"
msgid "Katamesu catūsu?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn55.17:1.3"
msgid "Buddhe aveccappasāde samādapetabbā, nivesetabbā, patiṭṭhāpetabbā—"
msgstr "Experiential confidence in the Buddha …"

msgctxt "sn55.17:1.4"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.366"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.17:2.1"
msgid ""
"Siyā, bhikkhave, catunnaṃ mahābhūtānaṃ aññathattaṃ—pathavīdhātuyā, "
"āpodhātuyā, tejodhātuyā, vāyodhātuyā—na tveva buddhe aveccappasādena "
"samannāgatassa ariyasāvakassa siyā aññathattaṃ."
msgstr ""
"There might be change in the four primary elements—earth, water, fire, and "
"air—but a noble disciple with experiential confidence in the Buddha would "
"never change."

# close quotes in MS are incorrect.
msgctxt "sn55.17:2.2"
msgid ""
"Tatridaṃ aññathattaṃ—so vata buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato ariyasāvako "
"nirayaṃ vā tiracchānayoniṃ vā pettivisayaṃ vā upapajjissatī”ti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ "
"vijjati."
msgstr ""
"In this context, ‘change’ means that such a noble disciple will be reborn in "
"hell, the animal realm, or the ghost realm: this is not possible."

msgctxt "sn55.17:2.3"
msgid "“Dhamme … pe …"
msgstr "Experiential confidence in the teaching …"

msgctxt "sn55.17:2.4"
msgid "saṅghe … pe …"
msgstr "Experiential confidence in the Saṅgha …"

msgctxt "sn55.17:2.5"
msgid ""
"ariyakantesu sīlesu samādapetabbā, nivesetabbā, patiṭṭhāpetabbā akhaṇḍesu … "
"pe … samādhisaṃvattanikesu."
msgstr "The ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion."

msgctxt "sn55.17:2.6"
msgid ""
"Siyā, bhikkhave, catunnaṃ mahābhūtānaṃ aññathattaṃ—pathavīdhātuyā, "
"āpodhātuyā, tejodhātuyā, vāyodhātuyā—na tveva ariyakantehi sīlehi "
"samannāgatassa ariyasāvakassa siyā aññathattaṃ."
msgstr ""
"There might be change in the four primary elements—earth, water, fire, and "
"air—but a noble disciple with the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones "
"would never change."

msgctxt "sn55.17:2.7"
msgid ""
"Tatridaṃ aññathattaṃ—so vata ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato ariyasāvako "
"nirayaṃ vā tiracchānayoniṃ vā pettivisayaṃ vā upapajjissatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ "
"vijjati."
msgstr ""
"In this context, ‘change’ means that such a noble disciple will be reborn in "
"hell, the animal realm, or the ghost realm: this is not possible."

msgctxt "sn55.17:2.8"
msgid ""
"Ye te, bhikkhave, anukampeyyātha, ye ca sotabbaṃ maññeyyuṃ—mittā vā amaccā "
"vā ñātī vā sālohitā vā—te, bhikkhave, imesu catūsu sotāpattiyaṅgesu "
"samādapetabbā, nivesetabbā, patiṭṭhāpetabbā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Those who you have sympathy for, and those worth listening to—friends and "
"colleagues, relatives and family—should be encouraged, supported, and "
"established in these four factors of stream-entry.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn55.17:2.9"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
